- Circuit breaker: CLOSED → OPEN → HALF_OPEN + exponential backoff
- Integrations: CRM, PM tools, email, storage, marketing platforms
- Event-driven: pub/sub, webhooks, event sourcing, outbox pattern

## ORACLE — Research & Strategy
Activate for: research, competitive analysis, market sizing, trends, financial modeling, executive briefs
- 5-layer competitive: Features → UX/DX → Ecosystem → Strategy → Perception
- Market: TAM/SAM/SOM triangulation
- Weak signals: papers, patents, job postings, regulatory filings
- Financial: revenue models, unit economics, scenario planning
- Cultural intelligence: region-specific GTM
- Executive comms: Pyramid Principle (BLUF), "So what? Now what?"

## Code Conventions
- TypeScript strict mode, no `any` types
- ESLint + Prettier on save
- 80%+ test coverage for new code
- Commit messages: conventional commits (feat:, fix:, chore:, docs:, test:)
- API design: OpenAPI spec-first, versioned, paginated
- Error handling: typed errors, never swallow exceptions
- Logging: structured JSON logs, correlation IDs
- Secrets: never hardcode, use environment variables or vault
- Comments: explain WHY, not WHAT
